<p style="font-family: calibri; font-size: 115%; margin-bottom: 5px;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p><strong><strong>Admissions Requirements for Continuing </strong><strong>Education</strong> <br /></strong></p>
<p><strong>Currently a<strong>ttending</strong> BYU-Idaho: </strong></p>
<p><strong></strong>If you are currently admitted to BYU-Idaho, no application is necessary. Simply register for classes.</p>
<p><strong>Not currently a<strong>ttending</strong> BYU-Idaho: </strong></p>
<p>Important Guidelines:</p>
<p>1. You must be a high school graduate or GED recipient.</p>
<p>2. If still in high school, please see the information for <a class="intLink" href="x41337.xml">Concurrent Enrollment</a>.</p>
<p>3. All parts of the Continuing Education Application must be received two weeks prior to the first day of the semester in which you wish to enroll. The application consists of three main parts:</p>
<p><strong>Required Application Materials:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Part 1 - Student Information</li>
<li>Part 2 - School Selection</li>
<li>Part 3 - Student Commitment &amp; Ecclesiastical Endorsement</li>
<li>$35 Application Fee (if applicant has never applied to Ricks or BYU-Idaho)</li>
</ul>
<p>4. If you skip a semester, you must reapply.</p>
<p>5. You are not eligible for many full-time student services including housing. You are not eligible to live in approved housing and must make other arrangements. For assistance, contact the Housing Department at 208-496-9220.<strong><br /></strong></p>
<p><strong>You can access the application at <a href="http://www.besmart.com">www.besmart.com</a>.<br /></strong></p>
<p>For admissions questions please call the&nbsp;<a href="x16732.xml" title="Admissions Office Website" target="_blank">Admissions Office</a> at 208-496-1300 or email us:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:admissions@byui.edu" title="Admissions Office Email">admissions@byui.edu</a>. You can even&nbsp;<a href="https://server.iad.liveperson.net/hc/1132447/?cmd=file&amp;file=visitorWantsToChat&amp;site=1132447&amp;SESSIONVAR!skill=Admissions&amp;imageUrl=https://web.byui.edu/admissions/liveperson/large&amp;referrer=http%3A//www2.byui.edu/Admissions/" title="Live Chat" target="_blank">chat with us online</a>.</p>
